<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="s4fq2g" data-video-descrip="During the Vietnam War, North Korean broadcaster Hanoi Hannah attempts to undermine black troops by questioning why they fight overseas for a country that has such deeply-instituted racism. " data-video-title="Hanoi Hannah" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/s4fq2g_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/s4fq2g.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/TokyoRose" data-video-tropename="Tokyo Rose" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="3.00" data-video-rating-count="2" data-video-media-sources="Creator/NgoThanhVan,Film/Da5Bloods" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link featured-widget-vid">
